description:
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting for a full time, 10PA Specialty Doctor with a complimentary special interest e.g. Glaucoma or Paediatric Ophthalmology to join our expanding and progressive team of ophthalmic surgeons. This post is fixed term for a duration of 24 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will provide a range of ophthalmic services in the department’s main sites. These will include general clinics and eye casualty as well as laser or other treatment/diagnostic clinics according to the surgeon’s abilities. In addition, specialist clinics and cataract or specialist theatre lists may also be available for suitable candidates. The appointees may also have responsibilities for inpatient cases and on-call as well as appropriate liaison with relevant allied specialties. Training and supervision is provided by our consultant team and in time the post-holders will be expected to work independently in appropriate areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is expected that the post-holder will be available to commence this post as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
